description:
SYNLAB è una multinazionale, presente in Europa, Asia, Africa e Sud America, composta da quasi 30 mila dipendenti, che collaborano con il principale obiettivo di migliorare il benessere dei pazienti.


In Italia, con un team di oltre 4 mila professionisti, **SYNLAB rappresenta il più importante e vasto gruppo di diagnostica integrata nei Medical Center e il più importante interlocutore dei servizi di Laboratorio**. Lombardia, Veneto, Friuli\-Venezia Giulia, Toscana, Emilia\-Romagna, Liguria, Lazio e Campania sono le regioni in cui si sviluppa principalmente l'attività di SYNLAB che è comunque presente in tutta Italia con partner accreditati.



La Mission: **fornire informazioni diagnostiche utili per una vita sana e per il benessere di tutti**.


La Vision: **una leadership conquistata attraverso l’eccellenza del servizio a favore delle persone e della comunità medica, con una diagnostica di altissima qualità**.


I Valori: **passione, responsabilità e customer centricity.**



Scopri di più: https://www.synlab.it





**Posizione:**
--------------

For the Operations team of SYNLAB Italia, we are looking for a **Lean Manager** who will be responsible for leading continuous improvement initiatives and contributing to processes transformation across Italy.


The position does not include direct people management, and requires a strong cross\-functional leadership on projects and a constant interaction with diverse stakeholders, like country and corporate functions, as well as international counterparts.


We are looking for a pragmatic, energetic, and assertive person—not a back\-office or purely analytical profile, but a true change agent who can work directly on processes, engage people, and deliver tangible improvements in efficiency, performance, and ways of working.

 **Contract and package**


Permanent contract



CCNL Commercio – Level 1



Indicative gross annual salary range: €43,000 – €47,000 \+ MBO

 **Main responsibilities**


The person will be responsible for:

* Leading Lean projects and continuous improvement initiatives, leveraging the STS (SYNLAB Transformation System) methodology;
* Analysing operational processes, identifying inefficiencies, waste, bottlenecks and improvement opportunities;
* Defining and monitoring action plans, KPIs, milestones and targeted results;
* Facilitating workshops, problem\-solving activities, Kaizen events and on\-site discussions;
* Supporting process standardisation and the deployment of Lean/STS best practices;
* Supporting change, influencing stakeholders and operational teams even without direct hierarchical authority;
* Collaborating with the Group headquarters and with the Group STS community.

**Requisiti:**
--------------

The ideal candidate has:

* At least 7 years of experience in Lean, Operational Excellence, Continuous Improvement, Industrial Engineering or Process Improvement roles;
* Previous experience in structured industrial, manufacturing or production environments;
* Hands\-on experience in change management projects with measurable impact on processes, KPIs and people;
* Solid knowledge of Lean tools, including VSM, A3, PDCA, Kaizen, 5S, Standard Work, Visual Management and Root Cause Analysis;
* Excellent command of Excel and PowerPoint;
* Good knowledge of Microsoft SharePoint, Planner and Visio will be considered a plus;
* Excellent written and spoken English;
* Availability to travel across Italy, approximately 30% of the time.



Previous experience in regulated or complex industrial sectors, such as pharma, medical devices, chemical, food, packaging or automotive, will be considered a plus.

 **Soft skills**


The ideal candidate also brings:

* Strong drive and result orientation;
* Assertiveness and influencing skills;
* Energy, ambition and pragmatism;
* Hands\-on approach;
* Problem\-solving attitude and change management skills;
* Ability to engage people and constructively challenge the status quo.

**Altre informazioni:**
-----------------------

**What we offer**


The opportunity to join an international and evolving environment, with a role highly exposed to Operations processes and Lean/STS transformation initiatives within SYNLAB Italia.

 *The job offer is open to candidates of all genders, in compliance with Legislative Decree no. 198/2006, as amended and supplemented, and Legislative Decrees nos. 215 and 216/2003 on equal treatment.*

*Applicants are invited to read the privacy notice pursuant to Articles 13 and 14 of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 at the following address:* *https://www.synlab.it/privacy\-policy*

**Attività principali:**

* Gestione deviazioni relative agli aspetti di processo produttivo e metodi analitici;
* Eseguire le attività di batch record review;
* Redigere product specification file/similari;
* Partecipare attivamente alle ispezioni da parte di clienti e da parte degli enti regolatori supportando il Lead dell'unità;
* Preparare la documentazione per l'approvazione e il rilascio dei lotti di prodotti;
* Seguire le attività di area relative alla spedizione dei prodotti finiti;
* Coordinare le attività di area relative alla revisione ed emissione dei Master batch record;
* Predisporre la documentazione necessaria alle attività produttive di lotto prodotto;

**Requisiti:**

* Laurea in CTF/Biotecnologie o similari;
* Esperienza pregressa nel ruolo in ambito di produzione di prodotti sterili (almeno 2 anni);
* Capacità analitica e proattività;
* Buona conoscenza della lingua inglese

**Salary Range:** 34\.000€ \- 38\.000€

**Who We Are**  

*AGC Biologics is a global Contract Development and Manufacturing Organization with a strong presence in Italy. From our Milan site, we develop and manufacture life‑changing advanced biologics for some of the world’s most innovative pharmaceutical companies. Together with our team members across Europe, the U.S., and Japan, we deliver development and manufacturing of mammalian and microbial\-based therapeutic proteins, plasmid DNA (pDNA), messenger RNA (mRNA), viral vectors, and genetically engineered cells therapies. Across our global network, we are united by one mission: To work side by side with our customers in order to improve patients’ lives by bringing new biopharmaceuticals to market.*
